## Subject III - Exercise 1
### Problem Analysis
We need to determine if a number is abundant based on the sum of its divisors.

### Solution Approach
1. Calculate the sum of divisors for `n`.
2. Compare the ratio `S(n)/n` with all smaller numbers.
3. Return 1 if `n` is abundant, otherwise return 0.

### Answer
```cpp
#include <iostream>

int sumOfDivisors(int n) {
    int sum = 0;
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
        if (n % i == 0) {
            sum += i;
        }
    }
    return sum;
}

int abundent(int n) {
    double ratio_n = static_cast<double>(sumOfDivisors(n)) / n;
    for (int k = 1; k < n; ++k) {
        double ratio_k = static_cast<double>(sumOfDivisors(k)) / k;
        if (ratio_k >= ratio_n) {
            return 0;
        }
    }
    return 1;
}

int main() {
    int n = 6;
    std::cout << "Is " << n << " abundant? " << abundent(n) << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```

