## Subject III - Exercise 3
### Problem Analysis
We need to count two-digit numbers that appear equally as prefixes and suffixes in a file.

### Solution Approach
1. Read numbers from the file.
2. Count occurrences of two-digit numbers as prefixes and suffixes.
3. Compare counts and output the result.

### Answer
a. The algorithm reads numbers, extracts prefixes and suffixes, counts occurrences, and compares them efficiently using hash maps.

b. C++ implementation provided below.

### Code Solution
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <unordered_map>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::ifstream file("bac.txt");
    std::unordered_map<int, int> prefixCount, suffixCount;
    int number;

    while (file >> number) {
        std::string numStr = std::to_string(number);
        if (numStr.length() >= 2) {
            int prefix = std::stoi(numStr.substr(0, 2));
            int suffix = std::stoi(numStr.substr(numStr.length() - 2, 2));
            prefixCount[prefix]++;
            suffixCount[suffix]++;
        }
    }

    int result = 0;
    for (const auto& entry : prefixCount) {
        if (suffixCount[entry.first] == entry.second) {
            result++;
        }
    }

    std::cout << result << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```

