## Subject III - Exercise 1
### Problem Analysis
We need to implement a function that checks if a number is "abundant" according to the given definition: a number n is abundant if S(n)/n > S(k)/k for all k < n, where S(i) is the sum of all positive divisors of i.

### Solution Approach
1. Calculate S(n)/n
2. For each k from 1 to n-1, calculate S(k)/k
3. If any S(k)/k ≥ S(n)/n, return 0
4. Otherwise, return 1

To optimize, we'll calculate the sum of divisors efficiently.

### Answer
```cpp
int abundent(int n) {
    // Calculate S(n)
    int sum_n = 0;
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (n % i == 0) {
            sum_n += i;
        }
    }

    // Calculate ratio for n
    double ratio_n = (double)sum_n / n;

    // Check all k < n
    for (int k = 1; k < n; k++) {
        int sum_k = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= k; i++) {
            if (k % i == 0) {
                sum_k += i;
            }
        }

        double ratio_k = (double)sum_k / k;
        if (ratio_k >= ratio_n) {
            return 0; // Not abundant
        }
    }

    return 1; // Abundant
}
```

