## Subject III - Exercise 3
### Problem Analysis
We need to count two-digit numbers that appear the same number of times as prefixes and suffixes in a list of numbers from a file.

### Solution Approach
1. Read all numbers from the file
2. For each number, identify its prefixes and suffixes that are two-digit numbers
3. Count occurrences of each two-digit number as prefix and suffix
4. Count how many two-digit numbers have the same count as prefix and suffix

To make this efficient, we'll use arrays to count prefix and suffix occurrences.

### Answer
a. Algorithm description:
1. Initialize two arrays prefixCount and suffixCount to count occurrences of each two-digit number (00-99)
2. For each number in the file:
   - Extract all possible prefixes and increment their counts
   - Extract all possible suffixes and increment their counts
3. Count how many two-digit numbers have equal counts in both arrays
4. The algorithm is efficient because it processes each number only once and uses O(1) time for lookups and updates in the count arrays

b. C++ implementation:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    ifstream fin("bac.txt");

    int prefixCount[100] = {0}; // For numbers 0-99
    int suffixCount[100] = {0}; // For numbers 0-99
    int num;

    // Read numbers and count prefixes and suffixes
    while (fin >> num) {
        // Process prefixes
        int temp = num;
        while (temp >= 10) {
            temp /= 10;
            if (temp >= 10 && temp < 100) {
                prefixCount[temp]++;
            }
        }

        // Process suffixes
        temp = num;
        int power = 1;
        while (temp >= 10) {
            int suffix = temp % 100;
            if (suffix >= 10) {
                suffixCount[suffix]++;
            }
            temp /= 10;
            power *= 10;
        }
    }

    // Count two-digit numbers with equal prefix and suffix counts
    int result = 0;
    for (int i = 10; i < 100; i++) {
        if (prefixCount[i] == suffixCount[i] && prefixCount[i] > 0) {
            result++;
        }
    }

    cout << result;

    fin.close();
    return 0;
}
```
